  "justification": "This function precisely matches the described behavior. It identifies which cluster nodes satisfy all scheduling filter plugins by: (1) Computing the target feasible node count using numFeasibleNodesToFind, reducing to 1 if no extender filters/scoring plugins exist; (2) If no filter plugins are registered, returning the first N nodes from a round-robin offset (nextStartNodeIndex); (3) Otherwise, running filter plugins in parallel against nodes via a checkNode closure starting from the previous cycle's offset; (4) Using atomic counters (feasibleNodesLen) to track feasible nodes and canceling early once the target is reached; (5) Recording non-feasible node statuses into a result array during parallel execution and copying them into the diagnosis object afterward via diagnosis.NodeToStatus.Set; (6) Measuring and reporting total Filter extension point latency via deferred metrics emission using metrics.FrameworkExtensionPointDuration."
}

